    "body": "I did the `set -x PATH` (which erased the PATH) as well as `set -x PATH $PATH` (which kept it), and neither worked. Opening a new terminal and running `printenv` yields the correct path set as an environment variable.\r\n\r\nEdit: I should say it's especially fishy as well because the `git_branch` module works, but I don't know if that's reading a file or executing `git`. I'll look at the source code.\r\n\r\nEdit2: I don't think `git_branch` is calling `git` but I also can't be sure.",
